    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-05-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="259"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 18071/6–9.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Hill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-05-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 166.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your No. 223, of February 24 last,
                    and with reference to the department’s No. 106, of the 5th of that month,
                    relative to the military-service case of Mr. Gottlob Blickle, a naturalized
                    citizen of the United States of German birth, I now inclose the form of
                    statement forwarded by the embassy wherein Mr. Blickle furnishes the information
                    required by the German authorities before consideration can be given his
                    case.</p>
                <p>Mr. Blickle’s German passport is also inclosed for the use of the embassy.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
